{"title_page": "Fumiya Sankai", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Fumiya Sankai\n| native_name        = {{nobold|\u4e09\u6d77\u30d5\u30df\u30e4}}\n| image              = File:FumiyaSpottedMagEnhanced.jpg\n| caption            = Fumiya Sankai at the Spotted Magazine Photoshoot\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1995|3|19}}\n| birth_place        = [[Hamamatsu]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka]], Japan\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nickname           = {{Flatlist|Fumi<br/>\nHumi<br/>\nMaharrrr}}\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|*[[Vlogger]]<br/>\nActor<br/>\n[[Music artist (occupation)|Recording artist]]<br/>\nBusinessman\n}}\n| years_active       = {{Start date|2015}}\u2013present\n| agent              = S.cot Management ({{Start date|2017}}{{ndash}}present)<br/>\nABS-CBN StarHunt Management ({{Start date|2019}}{{ndash}}present)\n| height             = 170 cm\n| website            = {{Flatlist|\n{{Twitter|fumfumfum3}}<br/>\n{{Instagram|23shun_base}}<br/>\n{{Facebook| fumiyasankai238}}\n<br/><br/> \n[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCi7Ofw4sJynsacr_i6uk_lA/ FumiShun Base] <br/>[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCqyeyK2GSFpfp2FAhuEaoPA/ Hiragana FumiShun Base] <br/>\n[https://fumishunbaseshop.stores.jp/ FumiShun Base Official Shop]\n}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed        = yes\n| background   = solo_singer\n| instrument   = {{Flatlist|\n* Vocals}}\n| genre        = {{Flatlist|\n[[JPop]]<br/>\n[[Music of the Philippines|OPM]]}}\n| label        = [[Universal Music Japan]] (2019\u2013present) <br/> [[Star Music]] (2019\u2013present)\n| years_active = 2018{{ndash}}present\n}}\n| module2            = \n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Fumiya Sankai'''|\u4e09\u6d77\u30d5\u30df\u30e4|Sankai Fumiya|born March 19, 1995}} is a Japanese vlogger in the [[Philippines]]. He has been active in his YouTube Channel, '''FumiShun Base''', since 2015. His fame grew when he became the first pure Japanese official housemate in [[Pinoy Big Brother: Otso]], a reality TV show for Filipinos. The \"Konnichi-Wonder Vlogger ng Japan\", as he is called, finished in the 9-month running show as the 5th big placer.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/145051/meet-the-ultimate-big-four-of-pbb-otso-a738-20190804|title=Meet the Ultimate Big Four of PBB Otso|website=PEP.ph|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n\n=== 1995 \u2013 2017: Early life and career beginnings ===\nFumiya was born on March 19, 1995, in [[Hamamatsu]] [[Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka]] Japan.  He was raised alongside his three siblings: two brothers named Yuya and Shunya,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertainment.abs-cbn.com/tv/shows/pbbotso/photos/albums/34021519-in-photos-meet-the-handsome-brothers-of-konichi-wonder-vlogger-ng-japan-fumiya-sankai|title=IN PHOTOS: Meet the handsome brothers of Konichi-Wonder Vlogger ng Japan Fumiya Sankai!|last=Corp|first=ABS-CBN|website=entertainment.abs-cbn.com|access-date=January 31, 2020}}</ref> and one sister named Asami. He is the eldest in their family. \n\nAfter his High School graduation, Fumiya started living alone in [[Tokyo]] while pursuing his vocational degree in Hotel Management.\n\nHe joined the hospitality workforce after his graduation from vocational school and worked in a hotel in [[Shinjuku]] as a bell boy. He resigned from his hotel job after two years and decided to pursue his dream of establishing his own clothing line. \n\nHe thought that being famous would make his clothes sell faster and one way would be to become famous as a vlogger. He then started making YouTube videos.\n\n=== 2017 \u2013 Present: Life in the Philippines ===\nHaving observed their hotel guests, he realized that being able to speak English is important for his business plans. On the 28<sup>th</sup> day of April, 2017, he flew to the Philippines to study English.<ref name=\":3\">{{Citation|title=I'm back on YouTube!!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WCGuUXSewvc|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\n\nHe attended the [[Lyceum of the Philippines University|Lyceum of the Philippines]] in Manila for his English lessons. \n\nHe learnt of the PBB audition from his Filipino followers. He attended and documented his audition for his vlog content but he was able to pass all the screenings and became an official PBB OTSO housemate.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nAfter PBB, he stayed in the Philippines to pursue a career in show-business.\n<br />\n\n==Career==\n\n===YouTube===\n\nFumiya established his YouTube channel, '''FumiShun Base''', with his brother Shunya on December 2, 2015, but only posted their first video on September 6, 2016. \n\nWhile studying in the Philippines, he continued to upload videos in his YouTube channel as a means to update his parents of his whereabouts. \n\nHe started uploading YouTube contents for Filipinos on the 31<sup>st</sup> of May 2017. His first video was a reaction video of [[Sarah Geronimo]]'s [[Kilometro (song)|Kilometro]]. From then on, he started gaining Filipino followers.\n\nOn April 2018, his channel hit 100K subscribers awarding him with the YouTube Silver play button.<ref>{{Citation|title=MARAMING SALAMAT PO!!!!!!!!!!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0R9htbO1t6M|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> On March 7, 2019, he hit the one million subscribers mark, awarding him with a gold play button.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starcinema.abs-cbn.com/2019/3/7/news/fumiya-sankai-hits-1-million-subscribers-on-youtub-47849|title=Fumiya Sankai hits 1 million subscribers on YouTube! {{!}} Star Cinema|last=Admin|first=Star Cinema|website=starcinema.abs-cbn.com|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://push.abs-cbn.com/2019/3/7/fresh-scoops/pbb-housemate-fumiya-sankai-hits-1-million-youtube-203967|title=PBB housemate Fumiya Sankai hits 1 million Youtube subscribers {{!}} PUSH.COM.PH: Your ultimate showbiz hub!|last=TEAM|first=PUSH|website=push.abs-cbn.com|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\nSome notable vlogs were his song covers of [[I\u00f1igo Pascual]]\u2019s [[Dahil Sa'yo|Dahil Sayo]], [[Daniel Padilla]]\u2019s [[Simpleng Tulad Mo]], [[Juan Karlos Labajo|Juan Karlos]]\u2019 Buwan, [[Maja Salvador]]\u2019s Dahan Dahan, and [[Ex Battalion|Ex Battallion]]\u2019s [[Hayaan Mo Sila]] which was featured in [[Rated K]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/trending/03/18/18/viral-japanese-guy-covers-hayaan-mo-sila|title=VIRAL: Japanese guy covers 'Hayaan Mo Sila'|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ent.abs-cbn.com/videos/44040719-the-life-of-andre-lou-fumiya-and-yamyam-before-joining-pbb-226307|title=Rated K: The life of Andre, Lou, Fumiya and Yamyam before joining PBB {{!}} ABS-CBN Entertainment|website=ent.abs-cbn.com|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\n\nOther notable vlogs are his auditions to [[Pinoy Big Brother: Otso|PBB Otso]] in Araneta Cubao and Cebu.\n\nWhen the channel started, Japanese was the primary language used in his videos. English subtitles were added since most of his subscribers were Filipinos. After his stint in PBB, he shifted to a mixture of English and Tagalog. Subtitles were no longer added. \n\nThis posed a problem for his growing fanbase. With the growing demand from Japanese subscribers, he established the '''Hiragana FumiShun Base''' '''(\u3075\u307f\u3057\u3085\u3093\u3079\u30fc\u3059)''' YouTube Channel on April 13, 2020. This channel uses pure Japanese.\n\n===Business===\nFumiya\u2019s dream was to establish his very own clothing line. Most of his business ventures are aligned to this dream.\n\nFumiya opened the official shop for his YouTube channel on June 22, 2019. The shop features his original designs from when he started his channel. Items were sold out on the first week.\n\nHe also did a collaboration with Livertineage Japan. His designs were released for pre-orders on February 7, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B8Qk6PeJ16Q/|title=LIVERTINE AGE on Instagram: \u201c. Fumiya \u00d7 LIVERTINE AGE Collaboration Item . \u672c\u65e517\u6642\u3088\u308aFumiya\u3055\u3093\u3068\u306e\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u30a2\u30a4\u30c6\u30e0\u306e\u53d7\u6ce8\u4e88\u7d04\u8ca9\u58f2\u3092\u958b\u59cb\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01 \u4eca\u56de\u306e\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u3067\u306f\u534a\u8896T\u30b7\u30e3\u30c4\u3068\u9577\u8896T\u30b7\u30e3\u30c4\u3092\u3054\u7528\u610f\uff01\uff01 .\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\n\nFumiya opened FumiShun Base Hamamatsu, his first business venture, on February 16, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/FumishunB/status/1222120320766578689?s=20|title=2\u670816\u65e5(\u65e5)\u5348\u524d10\u6642\u306b FumiShun Base Hamamatsu \u304c OPEN|last=Base|first=FumiShun|date=2020-01-28|website=@FumishunB|language=ja|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> The establishment is a museum which exhibits Fumiya\u2019s memoirs from his childhood, life as a vlogger, and his life in the Philippines. FumiShun Base merchandise are also being sold.\n\nThe earnings of his museum will be used for charity.\n\n===Entertainment Industry===\n\n==== Philippines ====\nFumiya was already known as a creator but his fame rose when he became an official housemate of PBB Otso. He has since then been added as a regular cast in a sitcom, [[Home Sweetie Home|Home Sweetie Home: Extra Sweet]]<ref name=\":1\" />, and a prime time romantic comedy TV Series, [[Make It with You (TV series)|Make It With You]].<ref name=\":2\" /> \n\nHe has also appeared in several TV programs in ABS-CBN such as [[ASAP Natin 'To|ASAP]],  [[Magandang Buhay]], [[Rated K]], [[Minute to Win It (Philippine game show)|Minute to Win It]], [[Umagang Kay Ganda]], [[It's Showtime (TV program)|It's Showtime]], [[Gandang Gabi, Vice!|Gandang Gabi Vice]], and [[Tonight with Boy Abunda]]. He was also the [[Myx|MYX]]' Celebrity VJ for December 2019.\n\nOn April 2020, his first show as a host, Highway Harvest, became available through [[The Filipino Channel|TFC Online.]]\n\nHe has also released several singles under [[Star Music]]. ''Stay With Me this Christmas'' was at the top spot of the charts on the Christmas week of 2019.\n\nFumiya held his first major concert ('''Fumiya Amazing \u2018Di Ba?''') at the Music Museum last November 15, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.onemusic.ph/news/pbb-otso-ex-housemate-fumiya-sankai-to-hold-a-major-concert-4903|title=PBB Otso Ex-Housemate Fumiya Sankai To Hold A Major Concert|last=PH|first=One Music|website=One Music PH|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref> His guests included [[Alex Gonzaga]], [[AC Bonifacio]], [[MNL48]], [[Jeremy Glinoga]] and the rest of Team LAYF.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musicmuseum.com.ph/fumiya-amazing-di-ba/|title=Fumiya: Amazing \u2018Di Ba? \u00ab Music Museum Group|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B41yG5bjarT/|title=Star Events on Instagram: \"Ito na nga taraga! 1 day to go na lang, \"FUMIYA AMAZING 'DI BA?\" at Music Museum. ready na si @23shun_base ready na ba kayo?!\u2026\"|website=Instagram|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== Japan ====\nSimultaneous to his activities in the Philippines, he has also started being active with his PR in Japan. He has been featured in several newspapers in Shizuoka and has appeared in several TV shows in Japan:\n\n* Ohayou Nippon \u2013 NHK Japan, February 6, 2020\n* Tadaima TV \u2013 TV Shizuoka, February 17, 2020\n\nHe has also released several singles under [[Universal Music Japan]]. ''Sige Sige Bahala Na'' peaked at #4 in iTunes Philippines (#1 under the JPop category) and #97 in iTunes Singapore when it was released in August 28, 2019. \n\n== Health ==\nFumiya had an operation in 2015 for a [[Pneumothorax|collapsed lung]]. In December 4, 2019, while he was in Japan, he experienced the same symptoms prompting him to visit a doctor the next day. He was diagnosed again with a collapsed lung. His right lung was smaller due to the air pressure caused by several holes on his lung.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/12/11/19/ex-pbb-housemate-fumiya-sankai-to-undergo-lung-operation|title=Ex-'PBB' housemate Fumiya Sankai to undergo lung operation|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn December 11, 2019, he underwent a surgery to remove the part of his lung with the said holes. The surgery was successful and he stayed in Japan to recover.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/12/13/19/ex-pbb-housemate-fumiya-sankais-lung-operation-a-success|title=Ex-'PBB' housemate Fumiya Sankai's lung operation a success|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/lifestyle/health-and-fitness/148208/fumiya-sankai-feeling-better-after-lung-surgery-a722-20191216|title=Fumiya Sankai feeling better after lung surgery|website=PEP.ph|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref> He returned to the Philippines after 2 and half months of recovery.\n\n==Discography==\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Track\n! Details\n|-\n|2020\n|Pray\n|\n*<small>YouTube release date: April 18, 2020</small><ref>{{Citation|title=Pray - Fumiya #Stayhome #WithMe|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Panfqq4Z43I|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2019\n| Like A Dreamy Xmas\n|\n*<small>Release Date (digital platforms): December 6, 2019</small>\n*<small>Label: [[Universal Music Japan]]</small>\n*<small>YouTube release date: December 18, 2019</small><ref>{{Citation|title=LIKE A DREAMY XMAS \u2013 Fumiya [Official Music Video]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dWlWe4Dq3lg|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Stay With Me this Christmas\n|\n*<small>First Live Performance: Fumiya Amazing 'Di Ba?, November 15, 2019</small>\n*<small>Release date (digital platforms): November 19, 2019</small>\n*<small>Label: [[Star Music]]</small>\n*<small>YouTube release date: November 15, 2019</small><ref>{{Citation|title=Stay With Me This Christmas \u2013 Fumiya (Lyrics)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S4Nfxt5A-ac|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|Ikaw Ang Pinili ng Puso ko\n(with Yamyam Gucong)\n|\n*<small>First Live TV Performance: [[Pinoy Big Brother: Otso|PBB Otso]], March 24, 2019</small>\n*<small>Album: Ang Soundtrack Ng Bahay Mo</small>\n*<small>Release date (digital platforms): May 12, 2019</small>\n*<small>Label: [[Star Music]]</small>\n*<small>YouTube release date: June 17, 2019</small><ref>{{Citation|title=Ikaw Ang Pinili Ng Puso Ko \u2013 Fumiya x Yam Yam (Lyrics)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r_K8ZgiFvio|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2018\n| Sige Sige Bahala Na\n|\n*<small>Release Date (digital platforms): August 28, 2019</small>\n*<small>Label: [[Universal Music Japan]]</small>\n*<small>YouTube release date: October 28, 2018</small><ref>{{Citation|title=Sige! Sige! Bahala na! \u2013 Fumiya \uff3bOfficial Music Video\uff3d|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f1f5qpW-5fg|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Concerts and Tours==\n\n* Fumiyam in Singapore (October 20, 2019)\n* Fumiya Amazing \u2018Di Ba? (November 15, 2019)\n* A Beautiful LAYF in Baliwag (November 24, 2019)\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Digital===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role\n! Network \n! Reference\n|-\n| 2020\n|Highway Harvest\n| Himself\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[The Filipino Channel|TFC Online]]\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Highway Harvest {{!}} Let your journey on learning, earning, and meaning begin on April 9 on TFC Online!|url= https://www.facebook.com/TFCOnlineOfficial/videos/261499724862542/?vh=e&d=n|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role\n! Network \n! Reference\n|-\n| 2020\n|''[[Make It with You (TV series)|Make It With You]]''\n| Yuta Himura\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]\n|<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmo.ph/entertainment/liza-soberano-enrique-gil-croatia-make-it-with-you-a1031-20190924|title=LOOK: Liza Soberano And Enrique Gil Are In Croatia For Their Upcoming Teleserye, 'Make It With You'|last=Sep 24|first=Steph Esguerra Olarte {{!}}|last2=2019|date=September 24, 2019|website=COSMO.PH|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2019\n|[[Myx|''MYX'']]\n|Himself (Celebrity VJ)\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://myx.abs-cbn.com/amp/features/21230/fumiyam-myx-celebrity-vjs-for-december|title=FUMIYA And YAMYAM Are The MYX Celebrity VJs For December|website=myx.abs-cbn.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Home Sweetie Home|Home Sweetie Home: Extra Sweet]]''\n| Hiro Tanahashi\n|<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://entertainment.abs-cbn.com/tv/shows/homesweetiehome/show-updates/2019/05/10/67051019-toni-finds-a-new-family-in-home-sweetie-home-extra-sweet|title=Toni finds a new family in Home Sweetie Home: Extra Sweet|website=entertainment.abs-cbn.com|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Pinoy Big Brother: Otso]]''\n|Himself (Official Housemate)\n|<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/news-releases/pbb-otso-batch-2-features-housemates-with-incred?lang=en|title=\"PBB Otso\" Batch 2 features housemates with incredible stories {{!}} ABS-CBN Corporate|last=Corporation|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Accolades==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:75%;\"\n|-\n! Year || Category || Show || Organization || Result || Reference\n|-\n| rowspan=\u201c1\u201d | 2020\n| Most Promising Male Star\n|\n| VP Choice Awards 2020\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://villagepipol.com/five-nominees-vp-choice-awards-2020/|title=Five official nominees for Most Promising Male Star 2020|last=Baltan|first=Angela Grace|date=2020-03-19|website=Village Pipol|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2019\n| Best New TV Personality\n|[[Home Sweetie Home]]||[[33rd PMPC Star Awards for Television|33rd PMPC Star Awards for TV]]|| {{nom}}  ||<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rappler.com/entertainment/news/240883-list-winners-pmpc-star-awards-television-2019|title=LIST: Winners, PMPC Star Awards for Television 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| PUSH Awards Year 5: PUSH Newcomer of the Year\n|  || ABS-CBN: PUSH Awards|| {{nom}}  ||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pushawards.abs-cbn.com/|title=Who will win in this year's Push Awards|last=Corp|first=ABS-CBN|website=Push Awards Year 5|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|RAWR Awards: Newbie of the Year\n|[[Home Sweetie Home]]\n|LionHearTV|| {{nom}}  \n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lionheartv.net/rawrawards2019/rawrawards2019-cub/|title=RAWR Awards 2019 \u2013 CUB CATEGORIES|website=LionhearTV|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* {{YouTube|channel= UCi7Ofw4sJynsacr_i6uk_lA}}\n* {{YouTube|channel= UCqyeyK2GSFpfp2FAhuEaoPA}}\n* {{IMDb name|10381620}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sankai, Fumiya}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:ABS-CBN personalities]]\n[[Category:Star Music artists]]\n[[Category:People from Hamamatsu]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Fumiya Sankai\n| native_name        = {{nobold|\u4e09\u6d77\u30d5\u30df\u30e4}}\n| image              = File:FumiyaSpottedMagEnhanced.jpg\n| caption            = Fumiya Sankai at the Spotted Magazine Photoshoot\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1995|3|19}}\n| birth_place        = [[Hamamatsu]], [[Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka]], Japan\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| nickname           = {{Flatlist|Fumi<br/>\nHumi<br/>\nMaharrrr}}\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|*[[Vlogger]]<br/>\nActor<br/>\n[[Music artist (occupation)|Recording artist]]<br/>\nBusinessman\n}}\n| years_active       = {{Start date|2015}}\u2013present\n| agent              = S.cot Management ({{Start date|2017}}{{ndash}}present)<br/>\nABS-CBN StarHunt Management ({{Start date|2019}}{{ndash}}present)\n| height             = 170 cm\n| website            = {{Flatlist|\n{{Twitter|fumfumfum3}}<br/>\n{{Instagram|23shun_base}}<br/>\n{{Facebook| fumiyasankai238}}\n<br/><br/> \n[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCi7Ofw4sJynsacr_i6uk_lA/ FumiShun Base] <br/>[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCqyeyK2GSFpfp2FAhuEaoPA/ Hiragana FumiShun Base] <br/>\n[https://fumishunbaseshop.stores.jp/ FumiShun Base Official Shop]\n}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed        = yes\n| background   = solo_singer\n| instrument   = {{Flatlist|\n* Vocals}}\n| genre        = {{Flatlist|\n[[JPop]]<br/>\n[[Music of the Philippines|OPM]]}}\n| label        = [[Universal Music Japan]] (2019\u2013present) <br/> [[Star Music]] (2019\u2013present)\n| years_active = 2018{{ndash}}present\n}}\n| module2            = \n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Fumiya Sankai'''|\u4e09\u6d77\u30d5\u30df\u30e4|Sankai Fumiya|born March 19, 1995}} is a Japanese vlogger in the [[Philippines]]. He has been active in his YouTube Channel, '''FumiShun Base''', since 2015. His fame grew when he became the first pure Japanese official housemate in [[Pinoy Big Brother: Otso]], a reality TV show for Filipinos. The \"Konnichi-Wonder Vlogger ng Japan\", as he is called, finished in the 9-month running show as the 5th big placer.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/145051/meet-the-ultimate-big-four-of-pbb-otso-a738-20190804|title=Meet the Ultimate Big Four of PBB Otso|website=PEP.ph|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n\n=== 1995 \u2013 2017: Early life and career beginnings ===\nFumiya was born on March 19, 1995, in [[Hamamatsu]] [[Shizuoka Prefecture|Shizuoka]] Japan.  He was raised alongside his three siblings: two brothers named Yuya and Shunya,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertainment.abs-cbn.com/tv/shows/pbbotso/photos/albums/34021519-in-photos-meet-the-handsome-brothers-of-konichi-wonder-vlogger-ng-japan-fumiya-sankai|title=IN PHOTOS: Meet the handsome brothers of Konichi-Wonder Vlogger ng Japan Fumiya Sankai!|last=Corp|first=ABS-CBN|website=entertainment.abs-cbn.com|access-date=January 31, 2020}}</ref> and one sister named Asami. He is the eldest in their family. \n\nAfter his High School graduation, Fumiya started living alone in [[Tokyo]] while pursuing his vocational degree in Hotel Management.\n\nHe joined the hospitality workforce after his graduation from vocational school and worked in a hotel in [[Shinjuku]] as a bell boy. He resigned from his hotel job after two years and decided to pursue his dream of establishing his own clothing line. \n\nHe thought that being famous would make his clothes sell faster and one way would be to become famous as a vlogger. He then started making YouTube videos.\n\n=== 2017 \u2013 Present: Life in the Philippines ===\nHaving observed their hotel guests, he realized that being able to speak English is important for his business plans. On the 28<sup>th</sup> day of April, 2017, he flew to the Philippines to study English.<ref name=\":3\">{{Citation|title=I'm back on YouTube!!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WCGuUXSewvc|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\n\nHe attended the [[Lyceum of the Philippines University|Lyceum of the Philippines]] in Manila for his English lessons. \n\nHe learnt of the PBB audition from his Filipino followers. He attended and documented his audition for his vlog content but he was able to pass all the screenings and became an official PBB OTSO housemate.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nAfter PBB, he stayed in the Philippines to pursue a career in show-business.\n<br />\n\n==Career==\n\n===YouTube===\n\nFumiya established his YouTube channel, '''FumiShun Base''', with his brother Shunya on December 2, 2015, but only posted their first video on September 6, 2016. \n\nWhile studying in the Philippines, he continued to upload videos in his YouTube channel as a means to update his parents of his whereabouts. \n\nHe started uploading YouTube contents for Filipinos on the 31<sup>st</sup> of May 2017. His first video was a reaction video of [[Sarah Geronimo]]'s [[Kilometro (song)|Kilometro]]. From then on, he started gaining Filipino followers.\n\nOn April 2018, his channel hit 100K subscribers awarding him with the YouTube Silver play button.<ref>{{Citation|title=MARAMING SALAMAT PO!!!!!!!!!!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0R9htbO1t6M|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> On March 7, 2019, he hit the one million subscribers mark, awarding him with a gold play button.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starcinema.abs-cbn.com/2019/3/7/news/fumiya-sankai-hits-1-million-subscribers-on-youtub-47849|title=Fumiya Sankai hits 1 million subscribers on YouTube! {{!}} Star Cinema|last=Admin|first=Star Cinema|website=starcinema.abs-cbn.com|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://push.abs-cbn.com/2019/3/7/fresh-scoops/pbb-housemate-fumiya-sankai-hits-1-million-youtube-203967|title=PBB housemate Fumiya Sankai hits 1 million Youtube subscribers {{!}} PUSH.COM.PH: Your ultimate showbiz hub!|last=TEAM|first=PUSH|website=push.abs-cbn.com|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\nSome notable vlogs were his song covers of [[I\u00f1igo Pascual]]\u2019s [[Dahil Sa'yo|Dahil Sayo]], [[Daniel Padilla]]\u2019s [[Simpleng Tulad Mo]], [[Juan Karlos Labajo|Juan Karlos]]\u2019 Buwan, [[Maja Salvador]]\u2019s Dahan Dahan, and [[Ex Battalion|Ex Battallion]]\u2019s [[Hayaan Mo Sila]] which was featured in [[Rated K]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/trending/03/18/18/viral-japanese-guy-covers-hayaan-mo-sila|title=VIRAL: Japanese guy covers 'Hayaan Mo Sila'|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ent.abs-cbn.com/videos/44040719-the-life-of-andre-lou-fumiya-and-yamyam-before-joining-pbb-226307|title=Rated K: The life of Andre, Lou, Fumiya and Yamyam before joining PBB {{!}} ABS-CBN Entertainment|website=ent.abs-cbn.com|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\n\nOther notable vlogs are his auditions to [[Pinoy Big Brother: Otso|PBB Otso]] in Araneta Cubao and Cebu.\n\nWhen the channel started, Japanese was the primary language used in his videos. English subtitles were added since most of his subscribers were Filipinos. After his stint in PBB, he shifted to a mixture of English and Tagalog. Subtitles were no longer added. \n\nThis posed a problem for his growing fanbase. With the growing demand from Japanese subscribers, he established the '''Hiragana FumiShun Base''' '''(\u3075\u307f\u3057\u3085\u3093\u3079\u30fc\u3059)''' YouTube Channel on April 13, 2020. This channel uses pure Japanese.\n\n===Business===\nFumiya\u2019s dream was to establish his very own clothing line. Most of his business ventures are aligned to this dream.\n\nFumiya opened the official shop for his YouTube channel on June 22, 2019. The shop features his original designs from when he started his channel. Items were sold out on the first week.\n\nHe also did a collaboration with Livertineage Japan. His designs were released for pre-orders on February 7, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B8Qk6PeJ16Q/|title=LIVERTINE AGE on Instagram: \u201c. Fumiya \u00d7 LIVERTINE AGE Collaboration Item . \u672c\u65e517\u6642\u3088\u308aFumiya\u3055\u3093\u3068\u306e\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u30a2\u30a4\u30c6\u30e0\u306e\u53d7\u6ce8\u4e88\u7d04\u8ca9\u58f2\u3092\u958b\u59cb\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01 \u4eca\u56de\u306e\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u3067\u306f\u534a\u8896T\u30b7\u30e3\u30c4\u3068\u9577\u8896T\u30b7\u30e3\u30c4\u3092\u3054\u7528\u610f\uff01\uff01 .\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>\n\nFumiya opened FumiShun Base Hamamatsu, his first business venture, on February 16, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/FumishunB/status/1222120320766578689?s=20|title=2\u670816\u65e5(\u65e5)\u5348\u524d10\u6642\u306b FumiShun Base Hamamatsu \u304c OPEN \u3057\u307e\u3059\uff01\n\u7f36\u30d0\u30c3\u30b8\u3092\u304a\u6301\u3061\u306e\u65b9\u306b\u306fSP\u30d7\u30ec\u30bc\u30f3\u30c8\u3001\u305d\u3057\u3066\u30b0\u30c3\u30ba\u3092\u8cfc\u5165\u3057\u305f\u65b9\u306b\u306f\u826f\u3044\u4e8b\u304c\u3042\u308b\u304b\u3082...\n\u6570\u91cf\u9650\u5b9a\u3067\u9577\u8896\u306eT\u30b7\u30e3\u30c4\u3082\u8ca9\u58f2\u3059\u308b\u306e\u3067\u304a\u65e9\u3081\u306b\u203c\ufe0epic.twitter.com/wrjS25xZnJ|last=Base|first=FumiShun|date=2020-01-28|website=@FumishunB|language=ja|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref> The establishment is a museum which exhibits Fumiya\u2019s memoirs from his childhood, life as a vlogger, and his life in the Philippines. FumiShun Base merchandise are also being sold.\n\nThe earnings of his museum will be used for charity.\n\n===Entertainment Industry===\n\n==== Philippines ====\nFumiya was already known as a creator but his fame rose when he became an official housemate of PBB Otso. He has since then been added as a regular cast in a sitcom, [[Home Sweetie Home|Home Sweetie Home: Extra Sweet]]<ref name=\":1\" />, and a prime time romantic comedy TV Series, [[Make It with You (TV series)|Make It With You]].<ref name=\":2\" /> \n\nHe has also appeared in several TV programs in ABS-CBN such as [[ASAP Natin 'To|ASAP]],  [[Magandang Buhay]], [[Rated K]], [[Minute to Win It (Philippine game show)|Minute to Win It]], [[Umagang Kay Ganda]], [[It's Showtime (TV program)|It's Showtime]], [[Gandang Gabi, Vice!|Gandang Gabi Vice]], and [[Tonight with Boy Abunda]]. He was also the [[Myx|MYX]]' Celebrity VJ for December 2019.\n\nOn April 2020, his first show as a host, Highway Harvest, became available through [[The Filipino Channel|TFC Online.]]\n\nHe has also released several singles under [[Star Music]]. ''Stay With Me this Christmas'' was at the top spot of the charts on the Christmas week of 2019.\n\nFumiya held his first major concert ('''Fumiya Amazing \u2018Di Ba?''') at the Music Museum last November 15, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.onemusic.ph/news/pbb-otso-ex-housemate-fumiya-sankai-to-hold-a-major-concert-4903|title=PBB Otso Ex-Housemate Fumiya Sankai To Hold A Major Concert|last=PH|first=One Music|website=One Music PH|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref> His guests included [[Alex Gonzaga]], [[AC Bonifacio]], [[MNL48]], [[Jeremy Glinoga]] and the rest of Team LAYF.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.musicmuseum.com.ph/fumiya-amazing-di-ba/|title=Fumiya: Amazing \u2018Di Ba? \u00ab Music Museum Group|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B41yG5bjarT/|title=Star Events on Instagram: \"Ito na nga taraga! 1 day to go na lang, \"FUMIYA AMAZING 'DI BA?\" at Music Museum. ready na si @23shun_base ready na ba kayo?!\u2026\"|website=Instagram|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== Japan ====\nSimultaneous to his activities in the Philippines, he has also started being active with his PR in Japan. He has been featured in several newspapers in Shizuoka and has appeared in several TV shows in Japan:\n\n* Ohayou Nippon \u2013 NHK Japan, February 6, 2020\n* Tadaima TV \u2013 TV Shizuoka, February 17, 2020\n\nHe has also released several singles under [[Universal Music Japan]]. ''Sige Sige Bahala Na'' peaked at #4 in iTunes Philippines (#1 under the JPop category) and #97 in iTunes Singapore when it was released in August 28, 2019. \n\n== Health ==\nFumiya had an operation in 2015 for a [[Pneumothorax|collapsed lung]]. In December 4, 2019, while he was in Japan, he experienced the same symptoms prompting him to visit a doctor the next day. He was diagnosed again with a collapsed lung. His right lung was smaller due to the air pressure caused by several holes on his lung.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/12/11/19/ex-pbb-housemate-fumiya-sankai-to-undergo-lung-operation|title=Ex-'PBB' housemate Fumiya Sankai to undergo lung operation|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn December 11, 2019, he underwent a surgery to remove the part of his lung with the said holes. The surgery was successful and he stayed in Japan to recover.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/12/13/19/ex-pbb-housemate-fumiya-sankais-lung-operation-a-success|title=Ex-'PBB' housemate Fumiya Sankai's lung operation a success|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/lifestyle/health-and-fitness/148208/fumiya-sankai-feeling-better-after-lung-surgery-a722-20191216|title=Fumiya Sankai feeling better after lung surgery|website=PEP.ph|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref> He returned to the Philippines after 2 and half months of recovery.\n\n==Discography==\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Track\n! Details\n|-\n|2020\n|Pray\n|\n*<small>YouTube release date: April 18, 2020</small><ref>{{Citation|title=Pray - Fumiya #Stayhome #WithMe|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Panfqq4Z43I|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2019\n| Like A Dreamy Xmas\n|\n*<small>Release Date (digital platforms): December 6, 2019</small>\n*<small>Label: [[Universal Music Japan]]</small>\n*<small>YouTube release date: December 18, 2019</small><ref>{{Citation|title=LIKE A DREAMY XMAS \u2013 Fumiya [Official Music Video]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dWlWe4Dq3lg|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Stay With Me this Christmas\n|\n*<small>First Live Performance: Fumiya Amazing 'Di Ba?, November 15, 2019</small>\n*<small>Release date (digital platforms): November 19, 2019</small>\n*<small>Label: [[Star Music]]</small>\n*<small>YouTube release date: November 15, 2019</small><ref>{{Citation|title=Stay With Me This Christmas \u2013 Fumiya (Lyrics)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S4Nfxt5A-ac|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|Ikaw Ang Pinili ng Puso ko\n(with Yamyam Gucong)\n|\n*<small>First Live TV Performance: [[Pinoy Big Brother: Otso|PBB Otso]], March 24, 2019</small>\n*<small>Album: Ang Soundtrack Ng Bahay Mo</small>\n*<small>Release date (digital platforms): May 12, 2019</small>\n*<small>Label: [[Star Music]]</small>\n*<small>YouTube release date: June 17, 2019</small><ref>{{Citation|title=Ikaw Ang Pinili Ng Puso Ko \u2013 Fumiya x Yam Yam (Lyrics)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r_K8ZgiFvio|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2018\n| Sige Sige Bahala Na\n|\n*<small>Release Date (digital platforms): August 28, 2019</small>\n*<small>Label: [[Universal Music Japan]]</small>\n*<small>YouTube release date: October 28, 2018</small><ref>{{Citation|title=Sige! Sige! Bahala na! \u2013 Fumiya \uff3bOfficial Music Video\uff3d|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f1f5qpW-5fg|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Concerts and Tours==\n\n* Fumiyam in Singapore (October 20, 2019)\n* Fumiya Amazing \u2018Di Ba? (November 15, 2019)\n* A Beautiful LAYF in Baliwag (November 24, 2019)\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Digital===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:75%;\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role\n! Network \n! Reference\n|-\n| 2020\n|Highway Harvest\n| Himself\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[The Filipino Channel|TFC Online]]\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Highway Harvest {{!}} Let your journey on learning, earning, and meaning begin on April 9 on TFC Online!|url= https://www.facebook.com/TFCOnlineOfficial/videos/261499724862542/?vh=e&d=n|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n\n{| class=\"wikitabl