ees-vp-choice-awards-2020/|title=Five official nominees for Most Promising Male Star 2020|last=Baltan|first=Angela Grace|date=2020-03-19|website=Village Pipol|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2019\n| Best New TV Personality\n|[[Home Sweetie Home]]||[[33rd PMPC Star Awards for Television|33rd PMPC Star Awards for TV]]|| {{nom}}  ||<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rappler.com/entertainment/news/240883-list-winners-pmpc-star-awards-television-2019|title=LIST: Winners, PMPC Star Awards for Television 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| PUSH Awards Year 5: PUSH Newcomer of the Year\n|  || ABS-CBN: PUSH Awards|| {{nom}}  ||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pushawards.abs-cbn.com/|title=Who will win in this year's Push Awards|last=Corp|first=ABS-CBN|website=Push Awards Year 5|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|RAWR Awards: Newbie of the Year\n|[[Home Sweetie Home]]\n|LionHearTV|| {{nom}}  \n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lionheartv.net/rawrawards2019/rawrawards2019-cub/|title=RAWR Awards 2019 \u2013 CUB CATEGORIES|website=LionhearTV|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* {{YouTube|channel= UCi7Ofw4sJynsacr_i6uk_lA}}\n* {{YouTube|channel= UCqyeyK2GSFpfp2FAhuEaoPA}}\n* {{IMDb name|10381620}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sankai, Fumiya}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:ABS-CBN personalities]]\n[[Category:Star Music artists]]\n[[Category:People from Hamamatsu]]\n", "name_user": "Kulotchii", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBusiness", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fumiya_Sankai"}
{"title_page": "KF Naft\u00ebtari", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = KF Naft\u00ebtari \n| image = [[Image:Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb Club Logo.svg|150px|Logo]]\n| fullname = Klubi Futbollit Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb \n| nickname = \n| founded  = 1926\n| ground   = [[Stadiumi Bashkim Sulejmani]]<br>[[Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]], [[Albania]]\n| capacity = 5,000 \n| chairman = \n| manager = Fatmir Ba\u00e7aj \n| league   = [[Albanian Second Division]] \n| season   = 2018\u201319\n| position = [[Albanian Second Division]], Group B, 11th\n| pattern_la1=_whiteshoulders|pattern_b1=|pattern_ra1=_whiteshoulders\n| leftarm1=000000|body1=000000|rightarm1=000000|shorts1=000000|socks1=000000\n| pattern_la2=_blackshoulders|pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2=_blackshoulders\n| leftarm2=FFFFFF|body2=FFFFFF|rightarm2=FFFFFF|shorts2=FFFFFF|socks2=FFFFFF|\n}}\n\n'''Klubi i Futbollit Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb''' is an [[Albania]]n [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]], [[Albania]]. Their home ground is the [[Bashkim Sulejmani Stadium]] and they currently compete in the [[Albanian Second Division]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/teams/albania/kf-naftetari-kucove/3388/ Soccerway]</ref>\n\nNaft\u00ebtari means ''Oilmen'', with Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb being the center of the Albanian oil industry.\n\n==History==\nFounded in 1926, they first participated in the [[Kategoria superiore|Albanian Superliga]] in 1946 as ''Spartak Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb''. During the [[People's Socialist Republic of Albania|communist era]] they were first known as ''Puna Qyteti Stalin'', then ''Spartaku Qyteti Stalin'' and for most of the time ''Naft\u00ebtari Qyteti Stalin''. Naft\u00ebtari played their final season in the [[Albanian Superliga]] in [[1986\u201387 Albanian Superliga|1987]].\n\n===One year suspension===\nIn the 1987/88 season, Naft\u00ebtari qualified for a promotion/relegation playoff after finishing runners-up to second tier champions [[KS Lushnja|Traktori Lushnja]].<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/alba88.html Albania 1987/88] - RSSSF</ref> After losing the first match 1-0 away to Albanian giants and Ministry of Interior club [[FK Dinamo Tirana|Dinamo Tirana]], the second match in Qyteti Stalin on 5 June 1988 ended in riots and burning of the Dinamo team bus partly due to the fact that the game was led by a referee and assistants from Tirana. Dinamo also won the second leg and the riots led to the suspension of Naft\u00ebtari from playing football for a year and demotion to the third tier. Coach [[Pandi Angjeli]] and players Meta and Makashi were suspended for life and club manager and former goalkeeper [[Fatmir Ismaili]] was dismissed.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/speciale-revolta-e-kucoves-30-vjet-nga-ndeshja-qe-shkundi-sistemin-monist/ Speciale/ Revolta e Ku\u00e7ov\u00ebs, 30 vjet nga ndeshja q\u00eb shkundi sistemin monist] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n==Stadium==\n{{main|Stadiumi Bashkim Sulejmani}}\nThe stadium of Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb is located in [[Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]], [[Albania]]. The name of the stadium is [[Stadiumi Bashkim Sulejmani]]. It has a capacity of 5,000 spectators <ref>https://int.soccerway.com/teams/albania/kf-naftetari-kucove/3388/</ref>.\n\n==Supporters==\n===Rivalries===\nNaft\u00ebtari's biggest rivals are [[FK Tomori Berat|Tomori Berat]], with [[Berat]] only 20 kilometers down the road and with fans of both clubs working together in the textile industry during the 1970s.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/perparim-kovaci-pantera-e-beratit-qe-u-rebelua-per-nje-frigorifer/ P\u00ebrparim Kova\u00e7i, \u201cpantera\u201d e Beratit q\u00eb u rebelua p\u00ebr nj\u00eb frigorifer] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n==Players==\nA few of best players known through their history:\n[[Fatmir Ismaili]] Goalkeeper, Ramadan Gega Defender, Gezim Gega, Mikel Koroveshi Defender, Paskal Gaqe Defender, Mihallaq Bonjako Defender, Enver Hafezi Defender, Vasil Piperoni Goalkeeper, Sofokli Vasili Forward, Bashkim Xheka Midfield,  Bashkim Sulejmani Midfielder, Agim Prifti Midfielder, Engjellush Islami Forward, Vladimir Skuro Forward, Agim Metaj, Maxim Halilaj Forward, Ilia Dashi Midfield, Muharrem Doko, Besnik Duli, Edmond Voda, Dashnor Dume Midfield, Emil Xhyberi, Kostandin Lule, Lilo Shau, Arben Iliazi, Astrit Haxhiaj, Ylli Vrusho, Barjam Fraolli, Agim Meta, Aleksander Koci Forward, Romeo Kocani Forward. Daut Hoxha forward, Vasillaq Sotiri forward, Ismaili played once for the national team in 1973.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/e-verteta-e-neperkembur-e-ballkaniades-1946/ E v\u00ebrteta e n\u00ebp\u00ebrk\u00ebmbur e Ballkaniad\u00ebs 1946] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n===Current squad===\n{{updated|22 November 2017}}\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|pos=GK|nat=ALB|name=Albano Kora}}\n{{Fs player|no=2|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Ardit Lleshi}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Sajmir Gega}} (Captain)\n{{Fs player|no=5|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Florian Daci}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Enea Kajo}} \n{{Fs player|no=7|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Florian Kopa\u00e7i}} \n{{Fs player|no=8|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Endri Koroveshi}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Ardian Gega}}\n{{Fs player|no=14|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Redon Behari}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|pos=FW|nat=ALB|name=Romario Alushi}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|pos=FW|nat=ALB|name=G\u00ebzim Hyska}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Martin Gucaj}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|pos=FW|nat=ALB|name=Klajdi Pepa}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|pos=GK|nat=ALB|name=Kristian Gjini}}\n{{Fs player|no=13|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Gerald Bega}}\n{{Fs player|no=18|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Azis Pepa}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Anesti Marini}}\n{{Fs player|no=22|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Ardian Kaloshi}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kategoria e dyt\u00eb}}\n{{Kategoria Superiore}}\n{{Football in Albania}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Naftetari}}\n[[Category:Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Albania]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1926]]\n[[Category:1926 establishments in Albania]]\n[[Category:Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = KF Naft\u00ebtari \n| image = [[Image:Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb Club Logo.svg|150px|Logo]]\n| fullname = Klubi Futbollit Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb \n| nickname = \n| founded  = 1926\n| ground   = [[Stadiumi Bashkim Sulejmani]]<br>[[Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]], [[Albania]]\n| capacity = 5,000 \n| chairman = \n| manager = Fatmir Ba\u00e7aj \n| league   = [[Albanian Second Division]] \n| season   = 2018\u201319\n| position = [[Albanian Second Division]], Group B, 11th\n| pattern_la1=_whiteshoulders|pattern_b1=|pattern_ra1=_whiteshoulders\n| leftarm1=000000|body1=000000|rightarm1=000000|shorts1=000000|socks1=000000\n| pattern_la2=_blackshoulders|pattern_b2=|pattern_ra2=_blackshoulders\n| leftarm2=FFFFFF|body2=FFFFFF|rightarm2=FFFFFF|shorts2=FFFFFF|socks2=FFFFFF|\n}}\n\n'''Klubi i Futbollit Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb''' is an [[Albania]]n [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]], [[Albania]]. Their home ground is the [[Bashkim Sulejmani Stadium]] and they currently compete in the [[Albanian Second Division]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/teams/albania/kf-naftetari-kucove/3388/ Soccerway]</ref>\n\nNaft\u00ebtari means ''Oilmen'', with Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb being the center of the Albanian oil industry.\n\n==History==\nFounded in 1926, they first participated in the [[Kategoria superiore|Albanian Superliga]] in 1946 as ''Spartak Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb''. During the [[People's Socialist Republic of Albania|communist era]] they were first known as ''Puna Qyteti Stalin'', then ''Spartaku Qyteti Stalin'' and for most of the time ''Naft\u00ebtari Qyteti Stalin''. Naft\u00ebtari played their final season in the [[Albanian Superliga]] in [[1986\u201387 Albanian Superliga|1987]].\n\n===One year suspension===\nIn the 1987/88 season, Naft\u00ebtari qualified for a promotion/relegation playoff after finishing runners-up to second tier champions [[KS Lushnja|Traktori Lushnja]].<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/alba88.html Albania 1987/88] - RSSSF</ref> After losing the first match 1-0 away to Albanian giants and Ministry of Interior club [[FK Dinamo Tirana|Dinamo Tirana]], the second match in Qyteti Stalin on 5 June 1988 ended in riots and burning of the Dinamo team bus partly due to the fact that the game was led by a referee and assistants from Tirana. Dinamo also won the second leg and the riots led to the suspension of Naft\u00ebtari from playing football for a year and demotion to the third tier. Coach [[Pandi Angjeli]] and players Meta and Makashi were suspended for life and club manager and former goalkeeper [[Fatmir Ismaili]] was dismissed.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/speciale-revolta-e-kucoves-30-vjet-nga-ndeshja-qe-shkundi-sistemin-monist/ Speciale/ Revolta e Ku\u00e7ov\u00ebs, 30 vjet nga ndeshja q\u00eb shkundi sistemin monist] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n==Stadium==\n{{main|Stadiumi Bashkim Sulejmani}}\nThe stadium of Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb is located in [[Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]], [[Albania]]. The name of the stadium is [[Stadiumi Bashkim Sulejmani]]. It has a capacity of 5,000 spectators <ref>https://int.soccerway.com/teams/albania/kf-naftetari-kucove/3388/</ref>.\n\n==Supporters==\n===Rivalries===\nNaft\u00ebtari's biggest rivals are [[FK Tomori Berat|Tomori Berat]], with [[Berat]] only 20 kilometers down the road and with fans of both clubs working together in the textile industry during the 1970s.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/perparim-kovaci-pantera-e-beratit-qe-u-rebelua-per-nje-frigorifer/ P\u00ebrparim Kova\u00e7i, \u201cpantera\u201d e Beratit q\u00eb u rebelua p\u00ebr nj\u00eb frigorifer] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n==Players==\nA few of best players known through their history:\n[[Fatmir Ismaili]] Goalkeeper, Ramadan Gega Defender, Gezim Gega, Mikel Koroveshi Defender, Paskal Gaqe Defender, Mihallaq Bonjako Defender, Enver Hafezi Defender, Vasil Piperoni Goalkeeper, Sofokli Vasili Forward, Bashkim Xheka Midfield,  Bashkim Sulejmani Midfielder, Agim Prifti Midfielder, Engjellush Islami Forward, Vladimir Skuro Forward, Agim Metaj, Maxim Halilaj Forward, Ilia Dashi Midfield, Muharrem Doko, Besnik Duli, Edmond Voda, Dashnor Dume Midfield, Emil Xhyberi, Kostandin Lule, Lilo Shau, Arben Iliazi, Astrit Haxhiaj, Ylli Vrusho, Barjam Fraolli, Agim Meta, Aleksander Koci Forward, Romeo Kocani Forward. Daut Hoxha forward, Vasillaq Sotiri forward, Ismaili played once for the national team in s1973.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/e-verteta-e-neperkembur-e-ballkaniades-1946/ E v\u00ebrteta e n\u00ebp\u00ebrk\u00ebmbur e Ballkaniad\u00ebs 1946] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n===Current squad===\n{{updated|22 November 2017}}\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|pos=GK|nat=ALB|name=Albano Kora}}\n{{Fs player|no=2|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Ardit Lleshi}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Sajmir Gega}} (Captain)\n{{Fs player|no=5|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Florian Daci}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Enea Kajo}} \n{{Fs player|no=7|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Florian Kopa\u00e7i}} \n{{Fs player|no=8|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Endri Koroveshi}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Ardian Gega}}\n{{Fs player|no=14|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Redon Behari}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|pos=FW|nat=ALB|name=Romario Alushi}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|pos=FW|nat=ALB|name=G\u00ebzim Hyska}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Martin Gucaj}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|pos=FW|nat=ALB|name=Klajdi Pepa}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|pos=GK|nat=ALB|name=Kristian Gjini}}\n{{Fs player|no=13|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Gerald Bega}}\n{{Fs player|no=18|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Azis Pepa}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|pos=MF|nat=ALB|name=Anesti Marini}}\n{{Fs player|no=22|pos=DF|nat=ALB|name=Ardian Kaloshi}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kategoria e dyt\u00eb}}\n{{Kategoria Superiore}}\n{{Football in Albania}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Naftetari}}\n[[Category:Naft\u00ebtari Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Albania]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1926]]\n[[Category:1926 establishments in Albania]]\n[[Category:Ku\u00e7ov\u00eb]]\n", "name_user": "Serbianboy87", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KF_Naft%C3%ABtari"}
{"title_page": "Fireman's chair knot", "text_new": "{{Knot-details\n| name=Fireman's chair knot\n| image= Handcuff-knot-ABOK-1140-Hitch-finish.jpg\n| names= Chair knot, Man-O-War Sheepshank\n| caption= \n| type= loop\n| strength= \n| origin= \n| related= [[Handcuff knot]], [[Sheepshank]], [[Tom fool's knot]]\n| releasing= \n| uses= Makeshift rescue [[Climbing harness|harness]] or [[handcuffs]]\n| caveat= \n| abok_number= #1140\n}}\n\nA '''fireman's chair knot''' (or simply '''chair knot''') is a [[knot]] tied [[in the bight]] forming two adjustable, lockable loops.  The knot consists of a [[handcuff knot]] finished with a locking [[half hitch]] around each loop.<ref name=\"FSCHandbook\">{{Cite book|publisher=Comhairle Na Seirbh\u00eds\u00ed D\u00f3ite\u00e1in (Fire Services Council)|title=Fire-Fighter Handbook \u2013 First Edition''|url=http://www.environ.ie/en/Publications/LocalGovernment/FireandEmergencyServices/FileDownLoad,2138,en.pdf|date=April 2001|page=4.106|accessdate=2011-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320093832/http://www.environ.ie/en/Publications/LocalGovernment/FireandEmergencyServices/FileDownLoad,2138,en.pdf|archive-date=2012-03-20|url-status=dead}}</ref> The loops remain adjustable until the half hitches are tightened.\n\n==Usage==\n[[File:Firemans chair knot in use.png|thumb|200px|A fireman's chair supporting a person in a horizontal highline configuration]]\nThe knot was first introduced by the Victorian chief fire officer Eyre Massey-Shaw in 1876.<ref>{{cite book|last=Shaw|first=John|title=The Directory of Knots|publisher=Grange Books|place=Rochester|date=2004|page=74}}</ref>\n\nMade with suitable [[rope]] by qualified personnel this knot can be used as a rescue [[Climbing harness|harness]] capable of supporting a person while being hoisted or lowered to safety.  One loop supports the body, around the chest and under the arms, and the other loop supports the legs, under the knees.  Tied towards the middle of a line, one end is used for lowering and the other end can serve as a tagline, to control the victim's position with respect to hazards during the descent.<ref name=\"budult\">{{Cite book|first=Geoffrey|last=Budworth|title=The Ultimate Encyclopedia of Knots|location=London|publisher=Hermes House|year=1999|page=206}}</ref>  A snug fitting of this knot should restrain the victim, even if unconscious.<ref>[http://www.clubdeexploradores.org/pionnudos.htm Knots: The Art of Working with Knots and Strings] The Explorer's Club. Last accessed 06 Dec 2011.</ref>  The fireman's chair can also be used to move a victim laterally when used as a part of a tensioned horizontal highline system.\n\nThe fireman's chair knot is considered to be merely a makeshift harness, to be used when conventional [[rope rescue]] techniques are not available. It is rarely used by modern rescue teams.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of knots]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://gumroad.com/l/jYdX cheap fireman's chair knot 3d model]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Knots}}\n", "text_old": "{{Knot-details\n| name=Fireman's chair knot\n| image= Handcuff-knot-ABOK-1140-Hitch-finish.jpg\n| names= Chair knot, Man-O-War Sheepshank\n| caption= \n| type= loop\n| strength= \n| origin= \n| related= [[Handcuff knot]], [[Sheepshank]], [[Tom fool's knot]]\n| releasing= \n| uses= Makeshift rescue [[Climbing harness|harness]] or [[handcuffs]]\n| caveat= \n| abok_number= #1140\n}}\n\nA '''fireman's chair knot''' (or simply '''chair knot''') is a [[knot]] tied [[in the bight]] forming two adjustable, lockable loops.  The knot consists of a [[handcuff knot]] finished with a locking [[half hitch]] around each loop.<ref name=\"FSCHandbook\">{{Cite book|publisher=Comhairle Na Seirbh\u00eds\u00ed D\u00f3ite\u00e1in (Fire Services Council)|title=Fire-Fighter Handbook \u2013 First Edition''|url=http://www.environ.ie/en/Publications/LocalGovernment/FireandEmergencyServices/FileDownLoad,2138,en.pdf|date=April 2001|page=4.106|accessdate=2011-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320093832/http://www.environ.ie/en/Publications/LocalGovernment/FireandEmergencyServices/FileDownLoad,2138,en.pdf|archive-date=2012-03-20|url-status=dead}}</ref> The loops remain adjustable until the half hitches are tightened.\n\n==Usage==\n[[File:Firemans chair knot in use.png|thumb|200px|A fireman's chair supporting a person in a horizontal highline configuration]]\nThe knot was first introduced by the Victorian chief fire officer Eyre Massey-Shaw in 1876.<ref>{{cite book|last=Shaw|first=John|title=The Directory of Knots|publisher=Grange Books|place=Rochester|date=2004|page=74}}</ref>\n\nMade with suitable [[rope]] by qualified personnel this knot can be used as a rescue [[Climbing harness|harness]] capable of supporting a person while being hoisted or lowered to safety.  One loop supports the body, around the chest and under the arms, and the other loop supports the legs, under the knees.  Tied towards the middle of a line, one end is used for lowering and the other end can serve as a tagline, to control the victim's position with respect to hazards during the descent.<ref name=\"budult\">{{Cite book|first=Geoffrey|last=Budworth|title=The Ultimate Encyclopedia of Knots|location=London|publisher=Hermes House|year=1999|page=206}}</ref>  A snug fitting of this knot should restrain the victim, even if unconscious.<ref>[http://www.clubdeexploradores.org/pionnudos.htm Knots: The Art of Working with Knots and Strings] The Explorer's Club. Last accessed 06 Dec 2011.</ref>  The fireman's chair can also be used to move a victim laterally when used as a part of a tensioned horizontal highline system.\n\nThe fireman's chair knot is considered to be merely a makeshift harness, to be used when conventional [[rope rescue]] techniques are not available. It is rarely used by modern rescue teams.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of knots]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Knots}}\n", "name_user": "Zaripov999", "label": "safe", "comment": "add 